ic.html#IsAdicComplete\">IsAdicComplete</a> <span class=\"fn\">I</span> <span class=\"fn\">N</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">f</span> : <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">n</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a>) → <span class=\"fn\">M</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Module/LinearMap/Defs.html#LinearMap\">→ₗ[</a><span class=\"fn\">R</span><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Module/LinearMap/Defs.html#LinearMap\">]</a> <span class=\"fn\">N</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Quotient.html#HasQuotient.Quotient\">⧸</a> <span class=\"fn\">I</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HPow.hPow\">^</a> <span class=\"fn\">n</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HSMul.hSMul\">•</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Notation.html#Top.top\">⊤</a></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">h</span> : <span class=\"fn\">∀ {<span class=\"fn\">m </span><span class=\"fn\">n</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a>} (<span class=\"fn\">hle</span> : <span class=\"fn\">m</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LE.le\">≤</a> <span class=\"fn\">n</span>), <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Ideal/Quotient/PowTransition.html#Submodule.factorPow\">Submodule.factorPow</a> <span class=\"fn\">I</span> <span class=\"fn\">N</span> <span class=\"fn\">hle</span></span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Module/LinearMap/Defs.html#LinearMap.comp\">∘ₗ</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\">n</span></span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\">m</span></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">F</span> : <span class=\"fn\">M</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Module/LinearMap/Defs.html#LinearMap\">→ₗ[</a><span class=\"fn\">R</span><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Module/LinearMap/Defs.html#LinearMap\">]</a> <span class=\"fn\">N</span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">hF</span> : <span class=\"fn\">∀ (<span class=\"fn\">n</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a>), <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">I</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HPow.hPow\">^</a> <span class=\"fn\">n</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HSMul.hSMul\">•</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Notation.html#Top.top\">⊤</a>).<a href=\"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/Quotient/Defs.html#Submodule.mkQ\">mkQ</a></span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Module/LinearMap/Defs.html#LinearMap.comp\">∘ₗ</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\">n</span></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\">F</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/AdicCompletion/Basic.html#IsAdicComplete.lift\">lift</a> <span class=\"fn\">I</span> <span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\">⋯</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Uniqueness of the lift.\nGiven a compatible family of linear maps `f n : M →ₗ[R] N ⧸ (I ^ n • ⊤)`.\nIf `F : M →ₗ[R] N` makes the following diagram commute\n```\n  N\n  | \\\n F|  \\ f n\n  |   \\\n  v    v\n  M --> M ⧸ (I ^ n • ⊤)\n```\nThen it is the map `IsAdicComplete.lift`.\n","docLink":"./Mathlib/RingTheory/AdicCompletion/Basic.html#IsAdicComplete.eq_lift","kind":"theorem","line":734,"name":"IsAdicComplete.eq_lift","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/RingTheory/AdicCompletion/Basic.lean#L734-L754"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/AdicComp